## Module 6: Notification API

All endpoints require authentication via `Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>` header.  
Access: Any authenticated role (USER, ASSOCIATE, ADMIN).

---

### 6.1 Get Notifications

**Endpoint:** `GET /api/v1/notifications`

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

**Request Body:** _None_

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Notifications fetched successfully",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "e5f6a7b8-1c2d-4e3f-9a0b-1c2d3e4f5a6b",
      "title": "Booking Confirmed",
      "message": "Your booking for 'Luxury 3BHK Apartment' has been confirmed by the owner.",
      "type": "BOOKING",
      "is_read": false,
      "created_at": "2026-03-07T18:30:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "d4e5f6a7-0b1c-4d2e-8f9a-0b1c2d3e4f5a",
      "title": "New Message",
      "message": "You have a new message from Rahul Sharma.",
      "type": "MESSAGE",
      "is_read": true,
      "created_at": "2026-03-06T09:15:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "c3d4e5f6-9a0b-4c1d-7e8f-9a0b1c2d3e4f",
      "title": "System Maintenance",
      "message": "Scheduled maintenance on March 10, 2026 from 2:00 AM to 4:00 AM IST.",
      "type": "SYSTEM",
      "is_read": false,
      "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

> Notifications are returned sorted by `created_at` in descending order (most recent first).

---

### 6.2 Mark Notification as Read

**Endpoint:** `PATCH /api/v1/notifications/{id}/read`

| Parameter | In   | Type | Description                      |
| --------- | ---- | ---- | -------------------------------- |
| [id](file:///c:/Users/yamit/Downloads/Desktop/livanaFinalbackend/backend-services/src/handlers/listing.rs#301-372)      | path | UUID | ID of the notification to update |

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

**Request Body:** _None_

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Notification marked as read",
  "data": {
    "notification_id": "e5f6a7b8-1c2d-4e3f-9a0b-1c2d3e4f5a6b",
    "is_read": true
  }
}
```

> **Security:** The endpoint verifies that the notification belongs to the authenticated user.  
> Attempting to mark another user's notification returns `403 Forbidden`.

